## 3. AUTK-PLOT: Interactive Charts

### Overview
`autk-plot` is a D3-based chart library for interactive visualizations. Charts consume GeoJSON feature properties and support linked views with `autk-map`.

### Installation

```bash
npm install autk-plot
```

### Configuration

All chart types share `PlotConfig`:

```typescript
import { Scatterplot } from 'autk-plot';

const chart = new Scatterplot({
  div: document.querySelector('#chart') as HTMLElement,
  data: geojson,           // FeatureCollection - properties used as data rows
  labels: {
    axis: ['area', 'height'],  // [x-axis, y-axis] property keys
    title: 'Building Area vs Height'
  },
  width: 600,
  height: 400,
  margins: { left: 80, right: 20, top: 40, bottom: 60 }  // Optional
});
```

### Chart Types

#### Bar Chart

```typescript
import { Barchart } from 'autk-plot';

const chart = new Barchart({
  div: document.querySelector('#chart') as HTMLElement,
  data: geojson,
  labels: {
    axis: ['neighborhood', 'population'],  // [categorical, numeric]
    title: 'Population by Neighborhood'
  },
  width: 600,
  height: 400
});

// Listen for clicks
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.CLICK, (selectedIds) => {
  console.log('Clicked row indices:', selectedIds);
});
```

#### Scatter Plot

```typescript
import { Scatterplot } from 'autk-plot';

const chart = new Scatterplot({
  div: document.querySelector('#chart') as HTMLElement,
  data: geojson,
  labels: {
    axis: ['area', 'height'],  // Both numeric
    title: 'Building Area vs Height'
  },
  width: 600,
  height: 400
});

// 2D brush selection
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.BRUSH, (selectedIds) => {
  console.log('Brushed rows:', selectedIds);
});
```

#### Parallel Coordinates

```typescript
import { ParallelCoordinates } from 'autk-plot';

const chart = new ParallelCoordinates({
  div: document.querySelector('#chart') as HTMLElement,
  data: geojson,
  labels: {
    axis: ['area', 'height', 'floors', 'year_built'],  // Multiple numeric axes
    title: 'Building Attributes'
  },
  width: 800,
  height: 400
});

// Axis brushes
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.BRUSH_X, (selectedIds) => {});
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.BRUSH_Y, (selectedIds) => {});
```

### Events & Interactivity

**PlotEvent types**:
- `CLICK` - Bar chart click
- `BRUSH` - Scatter plot 2D brush
- `BRUSH_X` - Parallel coordinates X axis
- `BRUSH_Y` - Parallel coordinates Y axis

```typescript
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.CLICK, (selectedIds) => {
  // selectedIds: array of row indices (by position in data.features)
});
```

### Linked Views

**Map → Chart** (selection highlight):

```typescript
import { MapEvent } from 'autk-map';

map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isPick', true);

map.mapEvents.on(MapEvent.PICK, (selectedIds, layerId) => {
  chart.setHighlightedIds(selectedIds);  // Highlight in chart
});
```

**Chart → Map** (thematic update):

```typescript
import { PlotEvent } from 'autk-plot';

chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.BRUSH, (selectedIds) => {
  map.updateGeoJsonLayerThematic(
    'buildings',
    geojson,
    (feature, index) => selectedIds.includes(index) ? 1.0 : 0.0
  );
});
```

**Full bidirectional example**:

```typescript
import { MapEvent } from 'autk-map';
import { Scatterplot, PlotEvent } from 'autk-plot';

// Setup
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isPick', true);
map.updateRenderInfoProperty('buildings', 'isColorMap', true);

const geojson = await db.getLayer('buildings');
const chart = new Scatterplot({
  div: document.querySelector('#chart') as HTMLElement,
  data: geojson,
  labels: { axis: ['area', 'height'] }
});

// Map → Chart
map.mapEvents.on(MapEvent.PICK, (ids) => {
  chart.setHighlightedIds(ids);
});

// Chart → Map
chart.plotEvents.on(PlotEvent.BRUSH, (ids) => {
  chart.setHighlightedIds(ids);
  map.updateGeoJsonLayerThematic(
    'buildings',
    geojson,
    (_f, i) => ids.includes(i) ? 1.0 : 0.0
  );
});
```

